#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: hello
version: 1.0.0
description: A minimal ScalaScript example
main: main
---

# Hello World

The simplest possible ScalaScript program.

## Greeting Function

```scalascript
def greet(name: String): String =
  s"Hello, ${name}!"
```

## Main Entry Point

```scalascript
def main(): Unit =
  println(greet("World"))
```

## Output

When run, this program outputs: `${greet("World")}`
